27/12/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic said on Monday (26 December) that the country hopes to obtain NATO assistance for a 12m-euro project to compensate laid-off army personnel. According to Radovanovic, BiH has applied for financing from the NATO Partnership for Peace Trust Fund. The project would be aimed at aiding some 11,000 people who are losing their jobs as a result of reforms that began last year. 
In other news, the leader of the main opposition Union of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD), Milorad Dodik, said on Saturday that he expects a new Republika Srpska (RS) government and budget in January. According to Dodik, SNSD has secured enough votes in the RS Parliament for a no-confidence motion against the cabinet of the Serb Democratic Party. (Dnevni avaz - 27/12/05; Fena - 26/12/05; Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 25/12/05; RTRS, PBS BiH - 24/12/05)
